                    <span>I read technical books by the armful, and I am used to the generally dry and meandering nature in which they tend to present material. This book truly has a mission to tell a story. If you have to get up to speed on ADO.NET quickly, and prefer not to be lulled to sleep by the SDK, this book is lively (well, considering the subject matter) and will truly convey an understanding that going over the class library won't do until you have written a lot of code.</span>
                  
              
